	<h1>Activation Context (1)</h1>

	A page can receive parameters. Specify the parameters in the method signature of the <em>activate</em> event handler. For example:
	
	<code><pre>
	void onActivate(Long personId) {
		this.personId = personId;
	}</pre></code>
	
	Tapestry calls these parameters the <strong>activation context</strong>.<br/><br/> 

	Here is a PageLink passing an activation context of <em>1</em>: 
	
  	<div class="eg">
		<t:pagelink t:page="examples/navigation/ActivationContext2" t:context="literal:1">Show Person 1</t:pagelink><br/>
	</div>
	
	The request is an HTTP GET with a URL like this: 
	<code>http://myhost/jumpstart/examples/navigation/activationcontext2/1</code><br/>
	PageLink extends the URL path with <em>/1</em>.<br/><br/>
	
	References:	
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/5.3/apidocs/org/apache/tapestry5/corelib/components/PageLink.html">PageLink</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/page-navigation.html#PageNavigation-PageRenderRequests">Page Render Requests</a>, 
	<a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/component-rendering.html">Component Rendering</a>, 
	list in <a href="http://tapestry.apache.org/property-expressions.html#PropertyExpressions-Grammar">Property Expression Grammar</a>.<br/><br/>

	<t:pagelink t:page="Index">Home</t:pagelink><br/><br/>
	
